      <title>Have To Execute Hexo With Sudo</title>
      <link href="/2024/11/15/have-to-execute-hexo-with-sudo/"/>
      <url>/2024/11/15/have-to-execute-hexo-with-sudo/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Have-to-execute-hexo-with-sudo"><a href="#Have-to-execute-hexo-with-sudo" class="headerlink" title="Have to execute hexo with sudo"></a>Have to execute hexo with sudo</h1><h2 id="Reason"><a href="#Reason" class="headerlink" title="Reason"></a>Reason</h2><figure class="highlight plaintext"><figcaption><span>hexo init``` is the reason.</span></figcaption><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">## Solution</span><br><span class="line"></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>sudo chown -R azureuser:azureuser &#x2F;path&#x2F;to&#x2F;hexo&#x2F;folder<br>chmod -R u+rwX &#x2F;path&#x2F;to&#x2F;hexo&#x2F;folder</p><pre><code>- change the /path/to/hexo/folder to that init executed. - remember do not ```sudo hexo init``` again. </code></pre>]]></content>
      
      
      
